## Docker Best Practices

### Multi-Stage Build (.NET 9)
```dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:9.0-alpine AS build
WORKDIR /src
COPY ["src/Services/Api/Api.csproj", "Services/Api/"]
RUN dotnet restore "Services/Api/Api.csproj"
COPY src/ .
RUN dotnet publish "Services/Api/Api.csproj" -c Release -o /app --no-restore

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:9.0-alpine AS runtime
RUN addgroup -S appgroup && adduser -S appuser -G appgroup
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app .
USER appuser
EXPOSE 8080
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s CMD wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "Api.dll"]
```

### Container Security
- Alpine base image (minimal attack surface)
- Non-root user ZORUNLU
- COPY specific files (ASLA `COPY . .` son stage'de)
- Multi-stage: build tools runtime'da YOK
- Image scan: `trivy image myapp:latest` CI'da
- Pinned versions: `FROM image:9.0-alpine` (ASLA `latest`)

## .NET Aspire Orchestration
```csharp
// AppHost/Program.cs
var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

var redis = builder.AddRedis("cache");
var sqlServer = builder.AddSqlServer("sql").AddDatabase("appdb");
var rabbitMq = builder.AddRabbitMQ("messaging");

var api = builder.AddProject<Projects.Api>("api")
    .WithReference(sqlServer)
    .WithReference(redis)
    .WithReference(rabbitMq)
    .WithExternalHttpEndpoints();

builder.AddProject<Projects.WebApp>("webapp")
    .WithReference(api);

builder.Build().Run();
```
- Service discovery otomatik
- Health dashboard built-in
- OpenTelemetry entegre (traces, metrics, logs)
- Local dev = Aspire, Production = Docker/K8s

## CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
```yaml
name: CI/CD
on:
  push: { branches: [main, develop] }
  pull_request: { branches: [main] }

jobs:
  build-and-test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4
        with: { dotnet-version: '9.0.x' }
      - run: dotnet restore
      - run: dotnet build --no-restore
      - run: dotnet test --no-build --collect:"XPlat Code Coverage"
      - run: dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive
      
  security-scan:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - run: trivy fs --severity HIGH,CRITICAL .
      
  docker-build:
    needs: [build-and-test, security-scan]
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - run: docker build -t myapp:${{ github.sha }} .
      - run: trivy image myapp:${{ github.sha }}
```

## Observability Stack

### Structured Logging (Serilog + Seq)
```csharp
Log.Logger = new LoggerConfiguration()
    .Enrich.FromLogContext()
    .Enrich.WithProperty("Application", "Api")
    .Enrich.WithProperty("Environment", env)
    .WriteTo.Console(new CompactJsonFormatter())
    .WriteTo.Seq("http://seq:5341")
    .MinimumLevel.Override("Microsoft", LogEventLevel.Warning)
    .CreateLogger();
```

### OpenTelemetry (Traces + Metrics)
```csharp
services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(b => b
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
        .AddEntityFrameworkCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddSource("MassTransit")
        .AddOtlpExporter())
    .WithMetrics(b => b
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddRuntimeInstrumentation()
        .AddProcessInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

### Health Checks
```csharp
services.AddHealthChecks()
    .AddSqlServer(connectionString, name: "database")
    .AddRedis(redisConnection, name: "cache")
    .AddRabbitMQ(rabbitConnection, name: "messaging");
app.MapHealthChecks("/health", new() { ResponseWriter = UIResponseWriter.WriteHealthCheckUIResponse });
app.MapHealthChecks("/health/ready", new() { Predicate = _ => _.Tags.Contains("ready") });
app.MapHealthChecks("/health/live", new() { Predicate = _ => false }); // liveness = app running
```

## SRE: SLI / SLO / SLA
```
SLI (Service Level Indicator) — olcum:
├── Availability: basarili request / toplam request
├── Latency: P50, P95, P99 response time
├── Error Rate: 5xx / toplam request
├── Throughput: request/second

SLO (Service Level Objective) — hedef:
├── Availability: > %99.9 (8.7 saat/yil downtime)
├── Latency P95: < 500ms
├── Error Rate: < %0.1

Error Budget = 1 - SLO
├── %99.9 SLO = %0.1 error budget = 8.7 saat/yil
├── Budget dolunca: yeni feature DURDUR, reliability'ye odaklan
```

## DORA Metrics
```
1. Deployment Frequency: Haftada 1+ (hedef: gunluk)
2. Lead Time for Changes: < 1 gun (commit -> production)
3. Change Failure Rate: < %15
4. Mean Time to Recover: < 1 saat
```

